ReportText: Chest, 2 views. History: Chest pain. Comparison: Chest x-rays last dated 10/17/2007. Findings: PA and lateral chest radiographs were obtained. The lungs are well aerated and clear. The cardiac, hilar, and mediastinal silhouettes are normal. There is no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. There are no acute bony abnormalities. Impression: Normal chest. The films and dictation have been reviewed with the Resident and I agree with the findings.
